Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.02,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Opening}
Comment: 0,0:01:29.99,0:01:30.03,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Part A}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.99,0:01:34.62,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Heads up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.79,0:01:41.46,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Yep, it's working.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.46,0:01:44.38,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Ugh, what the heck was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.38,0:01:46.92,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Automatic selection of targets for your technique?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.92,0:01:48.00,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:51.51,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Though, to be precise, I'm the target for the technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.51,0:01:54.72,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I've automated what I used to do manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.72,0:01:56.43,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,In addition to cursed energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.43,0:02:01.31,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,it can discern an object's danger level based on\N its mass, velocity, and shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.31,0:02:06.48,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,It'd be nice if it could detect poisons too,\N but that'll take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:11.61,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Now I should be able to keep my Limitless active\N almost perpetually with minimal resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.61,0:02:14.57,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Having it perpetually active will fry your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.57,0:02:18.74,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I'll also have reverse cursed technique\N running around the clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:21.20,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,constantly giving it a fresh brain to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:24.92,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I've finally minimized all the necessary hand signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.92,0:02:30.05,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Multiple simultaneous activations of Red and Blue\N is coming along nicely as well. {While it's technically correct, the whole thing is mind-messing. Maybe first two words have redundancy?} {multiple simultaneous is correct}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.05,0:02:34.18,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,The only things left are Domain Expansion\N and long-distance teleportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.76,0:02:39.68,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,If we set up a clear course around the school, \NI might be able to get that down too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.18,0:02:42.98,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Shoko, could you lend me some lab rats? {is he referring to the juniors?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.98,0:02:44.31,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.31,0:02:46.65,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Satoru became "the strongest."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.65,0:02:49.32,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Suguru, have you lost weight?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.32,0:02:50.65,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:53.65,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}He handled all his missions alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.65,0:02:57.28,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shoko was never sent out on\N dangerous missions in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:01.54,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}which naturally meant I was sent on missions alone more often too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.83,0:03:03.45,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,It's just heat fatigue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:04.75,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:07.29,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Had too much somen? {what is somen?}{noodles}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.79,0:03:11.25,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Things were busy that summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:19.85,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps due to all those frequent disasters last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.60,0:03:22.93,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Curses were springing up like maggots.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.43,0:03:25.18,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Exorcise. {originally this was joined and the next instance was split}{good}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:26.14,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Consume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.69,0:03:28.06,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:30.52,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Exorcise. Consume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:33.11,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a taste nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.11,0:03:34.49,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}The taste of a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.99,0:03:38.28,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like swallowing a rag used to wipe up shit and vomit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:42.41,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who am I doing this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:47.71,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Exorcise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.71,0:03:48.42,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Consume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:52.84,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've been telling myself ever since that day. {That's what I've been telling myself ever since that day.} {I prefer the one you put in comments, but maybe with a colon or a dash} {the order is flipped so it doesn't make sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.84,0:03:55.55,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}What I witnessed was nothing out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.55,0:03:57.63,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just the ugliness of the masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:04:03.85,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Despite knowing that, I still chose to be\N a sorcerer who saves others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.32,0:04:14.90,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't lose your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.90,0:04:17.36,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}Follow through with your duty as the strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:38.38,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Damn monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:43.10,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Geto{**-san}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:45.77,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:48.18,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I hope you're doing well!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:50.02,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You want a drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.44,0:04:52.61,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,What? No, I couldn't possibly...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.61,0:04:53.65,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Cola, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.61,0:04:59.65,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I'm going pretty far away for tomorrow's mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:00.91,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.91,0:05:02.37,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'll be expecting souvenirs, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.37,0:05:03.49,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.49,0:05:06.58,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Would you like something sweet or salty?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:11.17,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Satoru might eat some too,\N so get something sweet, I guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.58,0:05:12.79,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:20.59,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Haibara, do you think being a sorcerer\N was the right path?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:22.09,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Isn't it too hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:24.64,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.68,0:05:29.52,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I'm not one to think too hard \Nabout my path in life. {I'm not really one to think about things too deeply.} {can it be phrased better?} {this one has some background. he basically needs to say "path" here, so he can say the word "follow" in the next line, so geto can repeat the same phrase later on}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.52,0:05:34.15,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I'm satisfied as long as I can follow it \Nto the best of my ability! {It feels really good to be able to give my all to something I can actually do.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.15,0:05:37.19,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:39.24,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:45.45,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Are you Geto{**-kun}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.41,0:05:49.58,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,What type of women do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:52.46,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,May I know who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.87,0:05:55.25,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I like girls who eat a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:56.17,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:05:57.67,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Haibara... {oh god the disappointment in his voice...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:06:01.51,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,It's okay. She's not a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.51,0:06:03.68,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I'm a great judge of character!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.51,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You say that sitting next to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.10,0:06:09.10,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,Yes! {:thumbs_up:}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:13.60,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,He was being sarcastic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.94,0:06:16.06,Default,Haibara,0,0,0,,I'll be off, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:18.77,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Is he your junior?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.77,0:06:20.86,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's cute how frank he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.86,0:06:24.24,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,He should be more suspicious of people as a sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.24,0:06:27.83,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,So, are you not going to answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.37,0:06:31.20,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I need you to answer my question first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:32.33,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.33,0:06:35.54,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Special-grade sorcerer, Tsukumo Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.54,0:06:37.25,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Ring any bells?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:38.21,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:39.71,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You're the...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:42.09,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Oh, wow! What have you heard about me? {I'm the what?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.30,0:06:46.34,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You're the special-grade\N who never takes on any missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.34,0:06:49.47,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Just a waste who does nothing but\N wander around overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:52.60,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Man, I hate Jujutsu Tech.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.60,0:06:53.48,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's sulking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:55.31,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.31,0:06:59.40,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Though it is true that Jujutsu Tech and I don't see eye to eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.40,0:07:02.94,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,What they do here is treat the symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.94,0:07:05.36,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I want to treat the cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:07.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,How does that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.57,0:07:13.04,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Instead of hunting down curses,\N I want to create a world where curses are never born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.92,0:07:17.71,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Care for a little lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.29,0:07:20.67,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,What {\i1}are{\i0} curses to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.67,0:07:26.80,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,They're creatures that are formed from the\N build-up of cursed energy leaking from humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:28.26,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:33.06,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Therefore, we have two ways to\N create a world where curses aren't born.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.06,0:07:36.98,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,First is to eliminate cursed energy from all of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:41.07,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Second is to make it possible for every human\N to control their cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.07,0:07:44.82,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I thought the first one had a pretty good chance of working.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.24,0:07:47.20,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It even had a proof of concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:48.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:50.83,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's someone you're familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.83,0:07:52.41,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Zenin Toji.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.41,0:07:58.83,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I've seen several cases where Heavenly Restriction\N has reduced a person's cursed energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.83,0:08:00.96,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,but only to the level of a normal human.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.96,0:08:03.55,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,He was the only one to eliminate it entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.59,0:08:07.97,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,That wasn't the only intriguing thing about him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.51,0:08:14.22,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,He could perceive curses with his five senses\N even without any cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:16.43,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,By eliminating cursed energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:21.19,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,his body became sharpened to the point\N that he developed a resistance to curses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.19,0:08:23.69,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,He truly was superhuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:25.82,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Don't feel bad about losing to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:30.82,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I wanted to try studying him, but he blew me off. {??? what}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.82,0:08:32.70,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's a real shame we lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:38.46,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Cases of Heavenly Restriction are few and far between,\N so I'm currently favoring the second route.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.46,0:08:42.33,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,To make it possible for every human\N to control their cursed energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:46.88,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Did you know? Curses are never born from sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.01,0:08:52.64,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Obviously, that doesn't include cases\N where the sorcerer turns into a curse after death. {foreshadowing}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.39,0:08:57.85,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Sorcerers leak very little cursed energy\N compared to non-sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.27,0:09:02.56,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's partly due to the difference in\N consumption and capacity of cursed energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.32,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,but the main reason is its flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.32,0:09:09.53,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Sorcerers are always channeling\N cursed energy throughout their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:15.79,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,In layman's terms, if all of humanity were sorcerers,\N curses would never be born.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:21.37,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,In that case, why not just kill every non-sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.42,0:09:24.67,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Geto{**-kun}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:27.63,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,That {\i1}is{\i0} an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:29.34,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:34.30,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,In fact, that might be the easiest way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.85,0:09:40.68,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Keep culling non-sorcerers and force them to adapt\N into sorcerers as a strategy for survival. {ayo}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:48.44,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Basically forcing them to evolve using fear and danger,\N the same way birds gained wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:52.49,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I'm not crazy enough to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.49,0:09:55.57,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Do you hate non-sorcerers, Geto{**-kun}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:01.41,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.41,0:10:05.38,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I always thought sorcerers existed to protect non-sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:10.55,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,But lately, the value of non-sorcerers\N has been wavering in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.17,0:10:14.97,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,The preciousness of the weak. The ugliness of the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:18.47,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I can no longer tell the difference between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:22.89,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Part of me despises non-sorcerers,\N and part of me wants to reject that feeling.{\alpha&HFF&\fscx128}. {why did i do that...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:28.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,If being a sorcerer is like running a marathon, then I can't see what lies at the finish line. {My vision for what lies at the end of the marathon game of being a jujutsu sorcerer is so vague now}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.57,0:10:30.69,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I don't know how I truly feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:33.90,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,The answer is neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.53,0:10:39.66,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,You're not at that stage yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:42.16,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,The part of you that despises non-sorcerers,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:44.42,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,and the part of you that rejects it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.42,0:10:48.17,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,They're both just possibilities that you're considering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.17,0:10:53.01,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Whatever your true feeling is,\N it's something you have yet to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.93,0:10:58.18,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:11:01.18,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I was hoping I could talk to Gojo{**-kun}, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:03.06,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Looks like I missed him today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.64,0:11:06.90,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I hope the three of us can all get along\N as fellow special-grades.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:11.28,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'll pass that along to Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.61,0:11:14.32,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Oh, right, one last thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:17.20,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about \Nthe Star Plasma Vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.20,0:11:24.16,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Maybe there was another Star Plasma Vessel all along,\N or maybe a new one has been born.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:28.21,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Either way, Tengen is stabilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:33.46,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Of course. {I'm sure.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:37.38,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't get his type. {Okay, hear me out: tilde}{never}
Comment: 0,0:11:38.09,0:11:38.14,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:44.85,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,The mission was to exterminate a weak\N second-grade curse. It was supposed to be easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.81,0:11:50.81,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.49,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,The Birthplace Deity... {gonna assume it's in the same class of curses as Smallpox Deity except this one's not a special grade}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.62,0:12:02.24,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Faith of the locals made it stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.24,0:12:03.95,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,This was a first-grade case!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.04,0:12:09.71,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You need to rest for now, Nanami.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.21,0:12:12.21,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Satoru has taken over the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:17.59,Default,Nanami,0,0,0,,Why don't we just leave\N everything up to him at this point?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:22.22,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}If being a sorcerer is like running a marathon...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.52,0:12:26.60,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}What if all that lies at the finish line
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.44,0:12:31.81,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}is a mountain of corpses of fellow sorcerers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.28,0:12:44.70,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,What is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.12,0:12:46.54,Default,Man,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:49.46,Default,Man,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}These two are responsible for the latest incidents!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.25,0:12:53.21,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,No, they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.01,0:13:02.34,Default,Man,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}These two are crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:05.81,Default,Man,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}They attacked the villagers with their weird powers again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.31,0:13:09.44,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've already exterminated the cause of those incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.44,0:13:12.56,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}My grandson was nearly killed by these two! {did we just assume their gender?} {yes.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:13.69,Default,Nanako,0,0,0,,That's because he{\fscx180}—{\fscx}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.69,0:13:15.65,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}Shut up, you monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.65,0:13:17.74,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}You're just like your parents!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.74,0:13:21.11,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}I knew we should've killed you at birth!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.74,0:13:21.11,Cursed,Curse,0,0,0,,{\an8}It... It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:25.91,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}The part of you that despises non-sorcerers,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.91,0:13:27.95,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}and the part of you that rejects it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.95,0:13:30.16,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}Whatever your true feeling is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:34.63,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Let's step outside for a moment, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:37.42,Default,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}...it's something you have yet to decide. {If internal thoughts are italicized, why not this?} {this is treated as a flashback} {no, you're right}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:43.80,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}What is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:45.05,Default,Man,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.56,0:13:48.56,Default,Woman,0,0,0,,{\1a&H20&}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:17.17,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.05,0:14:20.17,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Don't make me repeat myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:22.17,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Suguru killed everyone in the village and{\fscx180}—{\fscx}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.17,0:14:24.13,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I heard you the first time!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.13,0:14:26.39,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,That's {\i1}why{\i0} I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:31.27,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Suguru's old house was empty as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.85,0:14:35.40,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Judging from the bloodstains and residuals,\N he might have killed his parents{\fscx180}—{\fscx}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.40,0:14:36.65,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Like hell he did!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.65,0:14:38.07,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:41.49,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,I don't understand what's going on, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:56.83,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Need a light?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.92,0:14:59.80,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,'Sup. {decaprio_pointing.jpg}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.88,0:15:02.67,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,If it isn't the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:04.09,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,What brings you here? {Need something?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.09,0:15:06.26,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Just testing my luck, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:10.89,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Any chance the charges are false?\NAsking just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:13.48,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Nope. Unfortunately not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:15.81,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,I'll ask another, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.81,0:15:17.23,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Why'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.23,0:15:19.36,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'm going to create a world of only sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:22.57,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Yeah, I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.57,0:15:24.32,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'm not a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:27.78,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I'm not holding out hope that everyone will understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:31.45,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Sulking over the idea\N that no one will understand you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.45,0:15:34.00,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,sounds pretty childish to me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.00,0:15:35.50,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Hey, Gojo?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:37.04,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Geto's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.67,0:15:39.17,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,Yeah, Shinjuku.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:42.63,Default,Shoko,0,0,0,,No way. I don't wanna get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:54.35,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Explain yourself, Suguru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:01.15,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You already heard from Shoko, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.15,0:16:03.32,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.32,0:16:06.61,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,So you're just going to kill everyone\N who's not a sorcerer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:07.82,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Even your parents?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.82,0:16:10.99,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I can't allow my parents to be an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.99,0:16:14.08,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Besides, my family isn't limited to just them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.08,0:16:16.37,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,That's not what I'm asking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:19.83,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I thought we weren't allowed to kill if there's no point to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:22.34,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,There {\i1}is{\i0} a point to it. Significance, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:23.67,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You could even call it a cause. {A cause, even.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:25.30,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Yeah, right! {Bullshit!} {There isn't!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:28.80,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Killing all non-sorcerers\N to create a world of only sorcerers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:30.18,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You {\i1}know{\i0} that's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.93,0:16:34.68,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,There's no point in chipping away at something\N you can't {\i1}possibly{\i0} do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:37.68,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,How arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:39.69,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:43.48,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You could do it, Satoru.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.90,0:16:47.99,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Yet you would try to convince someone else
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:52.91,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,that it's impossible to do something that's possible for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.12,0:16:59.79,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Are you the strongest because you're Gojo Satoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.79,0:17:02.58,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Or are you Gojo Satoru because you're the strongest?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:04.34,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,What exactly are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:11.13,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,If I could be you, wouldn't my foolish ideals \Nbecome reasonable possibilities?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.89,0:17:14.89,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,This is the path I've chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:17.64,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,All that's left is to follow it to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.11,0:17:28.86,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,If you want to kill me, then kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:32.61,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,There would be a point to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:44.63,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Why didn't you pursue him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:50.55,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You're actually asking me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:54.05,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,No, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:17:55.64,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:02.02,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,{*}Teach{*Sensei}, I'm strong, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.39,0:18:04.77,Default,Yaga,0,0,0,,Yeah, brazenly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.73,0:18:10.28,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Me being strong isn't enough, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.99,0:18:15.45,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I can only save those who allow themselves to be saved. {i wanna use "want to be saved" but "allow themselves" implies someone else is doing the saving (kinda?) which is intended}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.29,0:18:23.21,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,I thought the Star Religious Group was dissolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.21,0:18:25.92,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,It's a different group with similar roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.92,0:18:28.96,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,It still looks like a religious group on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.96,0:18:30.01,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,Don't like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.01,0:18:33.68,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,No, it doesn't matter as long as I can\N collect curses and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.09,0:18:36.60,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,Are you really going out dressed like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.60,0:18:39.35,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Why not? A little showmanship goes a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:41.48,Default,Nanako,0,0,0,,{*}Master Geto{*Geto-sama}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.48,0:18:42.73,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Watch closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.35,0:18:44.60,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,They're all there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.60,0:18:47.77,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,All the branch directors,\N representatives, and the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.77,0:18:49.86,Default,Kong,0,0,0,,All the big donors too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:54.57,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Check, check.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.11,0:18:58.53,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:19:00.29,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Now, I'll keep this brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.66,0:19:04.29,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,As of this moment, this organization belongs to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:06.46,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,We'll have a new name as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.46,0:19:09.17,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,So everyone, please be sure to obey me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:13.22,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Now, that's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.92,0:19:15.26,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.26,0:19:18.10,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{*}Mr. Sonoda{*Sonoda-san}, could you please come to the stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.18,0:19:20.93,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Yes! You there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.60,0:19:23.60,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,Now, let's try this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.23,0:19:25.60,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hate monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:27.52,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,You {\i1}will{\i0} obey me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.90,0:19:30.02,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,{\i1}That is the true feeling I chose. {i feel the "true feeling" should just be "feeling" but there's significance to the repetetion} {okay after looking into this a bit more i realized that the full meaning of this line is literally untranslatable so i'll just put in a tl note:} {the word he used here is 本音 (honne) where the individual characters 本 (hon) means true and 音 (oto) means sound/tone. geto has always used a polite tone, until this moment, where not only did he choose his "true feelings" but also his "tone"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.73,0:19:32.23,Default,Geto,0,0,0,,filthy monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.69,0:19:37.53,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You're Fushiguro Megumi{**-kun}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.87,0:19:41.20,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:43.37,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,And what's with that look on your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:47.71,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You look just like him, is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:50.17,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,My own issue. {Is there a better way to put this.}{waaaat it's one of the cr lines that i actually like}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.63,0:19:52.59,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,So, about your dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.59,0:19:55.59,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,He's from a big-shot sorcerer family\N called the Zenin clan,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:20:00.80,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,but the reason he ran away and had you\N makes him a scumbag even by {\i1}my{\i0} standards!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.80,0:20:05.52,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You have the ability to see the unseen,\N and the power to manipulate it as well, right? {he actually means to say he can see cursed spirits and has cursed energy}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.52,0:20:08.69,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You've noticed the talent within yourself too, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.69,0:20:11.36,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,The Zenin clan {\i1}loves{\i0} talent like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.36,0:20:14.53,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Most become aware of it at around\N four to six years of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.53,0:20:16.95,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,A ripe time to sell, indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.95,0:20:23.20,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You, my dear Megumi{**-kun}, are your dad's\N ace against the Zenin clan! {check tl} {yep, wrong. go fix it in s1 too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.20,0:20:25.04,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Pisses you off, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.04,0:20:29.17,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,So I took care of that dad of yours by ki{\fscx180}—{\fscx}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.79,0:20:29.17,Alt,Megumi,0,0,0,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.17,0:20:32.17,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,I have no interest in where he is\N or what he's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.17,0:20:35.55,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,Haven't seen him in years.\N Barely remember his face. {he legit went out to buy milk}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:38.51,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,Though I get the general idea\N from what you just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.51,0:20:41.68,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,Tsumiki's mother hasn't come home\N for a while now, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.68,0:20:43.68,Default,Tsumiki,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ah, Megumi's back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.35,0:20:49.10,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,That means they're done with us\N and are off enjoying themselves elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:53.06,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Are you really a first grader?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.69,0:20:55.11,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:20:58.28,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,If you ever wanna know about your dad,\N feel free to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.28,0:20:59.61,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Hup. {Upsie daisy?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:02.49,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,I think you'll find it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:04.20,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Now, on to the main point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.20,0:21:05.87,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,What do you wanna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.87,0:21:07.87,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Go to the Zenin clan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.50,0:21:10.33,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,What will happen to Tsumiki? {>happen}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:14.04,Default,Megumi,0,0,0,,Will she be happy there? It all depends on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.04,0:21:14.88,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.88,0:21:16.51,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,A hundred percent no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.51,0:21:18.13,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,That I can assure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:22.97,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:25.76,Default,Gojo,0,0,0,,You can leave it to me, then.
